[2] Kenya (Dadaab)
Date: Mon 12 Sep 2011
Source: Nairobi Star/All Africa Global Media via COMTEX [edited]
http://www.menafn.com/qn_news_story.asp?storyid=%7B8663a177-edb3-44ae-bc66-b6e53a251871%7D


Daadab [Dadaab] refugee camp has been identified as the source of the
current measles outbreak. Public Health Director Shariff Shaanaz
suspects the disease has spread from the camp where several cases have
been reported. He said they have launched an anti-measles campaign at
the camp to ensure the disease does not spread further.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It must be presumed that this report refers to the Dadaab (not
Daadab) camp. Dadaab is a semi-arid town in the North Eastern Province
in Kenya. As of 2011, it has been described as the largest refugee
camp in the world. Dadaab is located approximately 100 km from the
Kenya-Somalia border. Its location is shown in the map at:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dadaab. - Mod.CP]

