[4] Zambia (Luapula)
Date: Mon 12 Sep 2011
Source: AllAfrica.com, ex Times of Zambia [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201109121255.html


Chiengi district in Luapula province has recorded an outbreak of
measles, with 10 more patients treated for the disease. Both District
Commissioner (DC) Freeman Kaputo and district medical officer James
Zulu confirmed the development in separate interviews. Mr. Kaputo said
although the outbreak was serious, no deaths had been recorded in the
past 14 days in which the health authorities had been treating measles
cases.

Dr Zulu said cases of measles were being recorded in areas between
Chienge and Nchelenge districts. "We have cases of measles recorded in
areas bordering Nchelenge district, Kabwe and Puta areas," he said. Dr
Zulu said health personnel had put in place measures aimed at ensuring
that the disease did not spread to other areas. He said most of the
measles-affected areas were those which were not covered during the
international medical volunteers' agency Medicine Sans Frontiers
(MSF)'s measles vaccines distribution and sensitization campaigns last
July [2011].

The health campaigns in which the MSF volunteers distributed free
vaccines and conducted measles prevention sensitization were
prematurely completed last July [2011] because of hostility from the
villagers who accused the MSF team of being Satanists. This happened
after word went round that the MSF medical practitioners had arrived
to collect human blood and were pretending to be distributing vaccines
and carrying out health campaigns.

--
