[7] USA (New Mexico)
Date: Sun 17 2011
Source: The Republic, Associated Press report [edited]
http://www.therepublic.com/view/story/2a8ea94933434389ab1e7ed6eab1b6d9/NM--Measles-Lincoln-County/


The New Mexico (NM) Department of Health is investigating a
laboratory-confirmed case of measles in an infant male from Lincoln
County. The NM authorities say the origin of the baby's exposure still
is unknown. The child's name hasn't been released.

Health officials say it's the 3rd measles case in New Mexico so far
this year [2011]. They say they're working closely with the family to
identify anyone who may have been exposed to the highly contagious
disease so that more cases can be prevented.

The NM authorities recommend that anyone who is unsure of their
vaccination status or persons traveling outside of the country should
check to see whether they're up to date on all immunizations including
the measles vaccination.

--
